claim.claim-text:
A manufacturing method of a hot-rolled steel sheet, wherein cooling water is sprayed at an inside of a final stand (11g) on a lower process side of the final stand (11g) in a row (11) of hot finishing mills, to rapidly cool a rolled material;

a surface temperature of the rolled material is measured on an entry side of the final stand (11g), to obtain an entry-side surface temperature; and

one of (A) and (B):
(A) an entry-side target surface temperature, which is a target surface temperature of the rolled material at the measurement position of the entry-side surface temperature, is calculated from an exit-side target surface temperature, which is a target surface temperature of the rolled material on an exit side of the final stand (11g), based on: a temperature increase by a heat generated by rolling processing in the final stand (11g); a temperature reduction by contact of a work roll in the final stand (11g) with the rolled material; and a temperature reduction by air cooling in transportation from the measurement position of the entry-side surface temperature to the work roll of the final stand;
(B) a prescribed entry-side target surface temperature and the measured entry-side surface temperature are compared; and a command is sent to at least one of a coilbox, rough bar heater, descaler, and between-stand cooling device such that the measured entry-side surface temperature becomes the entry-side target surface temperature.

The manufacturing method of a hot rolled steel sheet according any one of claims 1 to 4, alternative (A), wherein a measuring device of the entry-side surface temperature is at least one of the following (a) and (b):
(a) a thermometer disposed at a position opposing to the surface of the rolled material; and as to the thermometer, a plurality of the thermometers are disposed in a sheet width direction of the rolled material, or one width direction thermometer is disposed;
(b) a water column thermometer comprising: a radiation thermometer disposed at the position opposing to the surface of the rolled material; and a water column forming device for forming a watercourse as a light waveguide between the rolled material and the radiation thermometer.

A manufacturing apparatus of a hot-rolled steel sheet comprising:
a row (11) of hot finishing mills;
an immediate rapid-cooling device (20), which is disposed on a lower process side of a final stand (11g) in the row (11) of hot finishing mills, and at least a part of which is disposed inside the final stand (11g) so as to be capable of spraying cooling water;
a device (40) for measuring a rolled material temperature, which is arranged in a manner capable of measuring a surface temperature of the rolled material (1) on an entry side of the final stand (11g); and
a target temperature arithmetic device (51), which calculates an entry-side target surface temperature being a target surface temperature of the rolled material (1) at a measurement position of the entry-side surface temperature, from an exit-side target surface temperature being a target surface temperature of the rolled material on an exit side of the final stand (11g), based on: a temperature increase by a heat generated by rolling processing in the final stand (11g); a temperature reduction by contact of a work roll of the final stand (11g) with the rolled material (1); and a temperature reduction by air cooling in transportation from the measurement position of the entry-side surface temperature to the work roll of the final stand (11g).

The manufacturing apparatus of a hot-rolled steel sheet according to any one claims 11 to 14, wherein the device (40) for measuring a rolled material temperature is at least one of (a) and (b):
(a) a thermometer disposed at a position opposing to the surface of the rolled material; and as to the thermometer, a plurality of the thermometers are disposed in a sheet width direction of the rolled material, or one width direction thermometer is disposed;
(b) a water column thermometer comprising: a radiation thermometer disposed at the position opposing to the surface of the rolled material; and a water column forming device for forming a watercourse as a light waveguide between the rolled material and the radiation thermometer.

The manufacturing method or apparatus according to any one of the preceding claims, wherein

the temperature increase ΔT1 by a heat generated by rolling processing in the final stand (11g) is determined using Formula (1); and/or

the temperature reduction ΔT2 by contact of a work roll of the final stand (11g) with the rolled material (1); is determined using by Formula (2); and/or

the temperature reduction ΔT3A by air cooling in transportation from the measurement position of the entry-side surface temperature to the work roll of the final stand (11g) is determined using Formula (3): Δ⁢T1=2c⁢ρ⁢h2⁢η⁢Gwr Δ⁢T2=2c⁢ρ⁢h2⁢λ⁢c⁢ρ⁢tRπ⁢TS⁢2-TR Δ⁢T3⁢A=2⁢σεc⁢ρ⁢h1TS⁢3⁢A+2731004-TA+2731004⁢t3⁢A+2⁢αAc⁢ρ⁢h1⁢TS⁢3⁢A-TA⁢t3⁢A

wherein c represents a specific heat (J/kg·K) of the rolled material (1);

p represents a density (kg/m3) of the rolled material (1);

η represents a heat processing efficiency;

G represents a roll torque (N·m);

r represents a diameter (m) of the work roll;

w represents a sheet width (m) of the rolled material;

h2 represents a sheet thickness (m) after the final stand (11g);

λ represents a thermal conductivity (W/m·K) of the rolled material (1);

tR represents the time (sec.) during which the rolled material (1) is in contact with the work rolls of the final stand (11g);

TS2 represents a surface temperature (°C) of the rolled material (1) during contact with the work rolls of the final stand (11g);

TR represents a temperature of the work rolls of the final stand (11g);

σ represents Stefan-Boltzmann's constant (W/m2·K4);

ε represents an emissivity (-) of the rolled material (1);

α A represents a heat transfer coefficient (W/m2·K) in an air-cooling area;

TS3A represents a surface temperature (°C) of the rolled material (1) in the air-cooling area; TA represents an air temperature (°C); and

t3A represents the time (sec.) for passing through the air-cooling area.
